<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Consul General at Batavia (
                        Foote
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d94</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">94</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-12-19T04:30:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-12-19T04:30:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-12-19T04:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-12-19T04:30:00-05:00" n="94" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d94">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.00/12–1946: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Batavia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foote</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Batavia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-12-19T17:00:00+07:30">December 19, 1946—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 20—12:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>486. For Vincent from Moffat: “If <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 436,
                    December 16, to Singapore<note n="80" xml:id="d94fn1">Not printed.</note> sent
                    before receipt my long telegram from Saigon,<note n="81" xml:id="d94fn2">Telegram 479, December 12; see footnote 78, <ref target="#pg_72">p.
                            72</ref>.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>, in light views expressed, may prefer my
                    return Washington as planned instead of proceeding Canberra. For reasons stated
                    feel settlement Vietnam question extremely difficult and conditions dangerous
                    with possibility deliberate Vietnam spread of conflict to Cambodia and Laos.
                    Believe possibility US assistance should be earnestly considered despite risk of
                    rebuff or unpopularity, especially in view apparent French confidence US
                    resulting from Siamese settlement.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Foote</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
